library("itsmr")
## Warning: package 'itsmr' was built under R version 3.4.3
x = ts(deaths)
plot(x)

acf(x,lag.max=40,type="correlation",plot=TRUE)

s=season(deaths,12) 
e=deaths-s
plot(ts(e))

acf(e,lag.max=40,type="correlation",plot=TRUE)

s=season(deaths,12)
y=deaths-s
m=trend(y,2)
e2=deaths-s-m
plot(ts(e2))

acf(e2,lag.max=40,type="correlation",plot=TRUE)

test(e2)
## Null hypothesis: Residuals are iid noise.
## Test                        Distribution Statistic   p-value
## Ljung-Box Q                Q ~ chisq(20)     55.38         0 *
## McLeod-Li Q                Q ~ chisq(20)     15.83    0.7272
## Turning points T   (T-46.7)/3.5 ~ N(0,1)        43    0.2993
## Diff signs S       (S-35.5)/2.5 ~ N(0,1)        35    0.8394
## Rank P           (P-1278)/102.9 ~ N(0,1)      1245    0.7483

The IID model is not rejected based on the correlogram because most of the bars are located within the dashed lines and the p-values provided by multiple test are all beyond 0.05.
xv=c("season",12,"trend",2)
a=arma(e,0,0) 
forecast(deaths,xv,a,h=24,opt=2)
